  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Has the 'Breathe, small steps matter' sticky note helped anchor your study days?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, it helps me start the day calm. I made a similar note for breaks: \"Pause, you’re doing well.\" Small reminders matter a lot.  \nBy the way, I tried a new dessert recipe yesterday—kulfi! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That's lovely. Short messages can be the best kind. Kulfi is a sweet win, especially homemade. How did it turn out?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It turned out aati! A little too sweet, but my family loved it. I think next time I'll cut down the sugar. Cooking helps me relax after study sessions. How about you, do you like to cook?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Your family sounds lucky! A little sweetness is worth the sugar fix. Cooking is such a good way to reset between study blocks. I like a good meal. What’s your next recipe going to be?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe something simple, like a lentil soup. Or maybe I'll try a new roti recipe. Still experimenting with flavors. You know, sometimes while cooking, my mind starts planning study schedules again... but at least it’s a calm kind of chaos. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — the kitchen is a space where thoughts still wander but feel lighter. A lentil soup could be just the thing for a study-day meal. What’s on your mind for tomorrow’s schedule?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tomorrow I’m focusing on mock tests—just 3 more before the big one. I’ve been nervous, but today’s practice went better, so I feel a bit more ummeed (hopeful). Maybe a nice roti and soup will follow after. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — mock test prep that intense is no joke. It's great to see the ummeed growing. Roti and soup after will be the best reward. How did today’s test feel different?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Today’s test felt less overwhelming. I managed time better, and I didn’t panic as much when stuck. Maybe I’m starting to get the rhythm. Still, my hands get shaky sometimes. But I’m trying to focus on progress, not just perfection. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s a real win — progress in rhythm is a big step. Shaky hands happen, but you’re learning to ride through them. What’s helping you stay calm when the nerves kick in?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I take deep breaths and repeat that sticky note — \"Breathe, small steps matter.\" Sometimes I also switch to a quick walk or a few minutes of playing my harmonium. It helps settle my mind. But honestly, just reminding myself that it’s okay to feel nervous helps too. 🙏"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s a beautiful mix — breath, movement, music, and kindness to yourself. All of it adds up. What’s one small step you’ll take tomorrow to keep this rhythm?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tomorrow, I’ll start with a 10-minute harmonium warm-up before the mock test. Music clears my head. Then I’ll stick to a short, focused study block—30 minutes, then a break with a short walk. Small, doable steps, just like you said. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — music first, then blocks. That rhythm sounds just right. What’s one thing you’ll do after the test to treat yourself?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "After the test, I’ll make myself a nice cup of chai and write down what went well — even small things. It’s my way of saying “well done” to myself. Maybe I’ll add a little star next to today’s date in my planner. 🌟"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s a lovely way to end — chai, reflection, and a star for today. Small wins deserve a celebration. What’s the first thing you’ll write down?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’ll write that I stayed calm when stuck on a question and tried a new time-management trick. Even if the answer was wrong, the step was right. Progress is progress, right? 🙏"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Exactly — steps matter more than speed. That calm choice is a win. What’s next after the test and chai?"
    }
  ],
